	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You take a crystal bead between your forefinger and thumb and describe a cozy hut. With a snap, you sent the bead spinning in mid-air. It hovers for a minute, as the glittering edges of the spinning crystal expand to form a hut matching your initial description, the interior of which becomes increasingly comfortable and dry.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>You create an &amp;reference[invisible] dome of force with a 10 ft. radius in the form of a hut. The hut has a single door, which is unlocked but can be locked with a padlock or magical lock. There are no windows.</p></li><li><p>The hut provides &amp;reference[total cover] to creatures within, making it impossible for most creatures to see them. A creature with &amp;reference[Truesight] sees the hut but not the contents of the hut. Creatures inside the hut cannot see outside: the hut is opaque from within.</p></li><li><p>The interior is comfortable and dry regardless of where it was conjured.</p></li><li><p>The dome has an AC of 15, 40 hit points, and has a damage threshold of 5 (meaning an attack must deal at least 5 damage to damage the hut).</p></li></ul>",
